cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on improving object recognition tasks using deep convolutional neural networks (DCNN) and large scale image datasets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for automatic labeling of images, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper leverages web data for dataset augmentation, which could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for contextual information extraction, which could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
